Business Brief -- Trans World Music Corp.:
   Earnings Increased by 24%
   In Fiscal Fourth Quarter
The retailer of prerecorded music and video products said
net for the year fell to $12 million from $14.5 million in
the previous year; weaker sales trends in the first half were
cited. Sales gained 15% to $411.1 million from $356.6
million.
   Trans World said it opened or acquired 60 stores last year
for a total of 597 outlets in the eastern half of the U.S.
   Trans World shares closed yesterday on the national
over-the-counter market at $24.50, bid.